The new attribute-filter validation is not tied to the reader snapshot that executes the filtered search, leaving a concrete race with projection reconfiguration that can surface the exact untyped vec0 column error the patch is trying to prevent.

Review comment:

- [P2] Validate attribute filters on the reader snapshot — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/orch-0.8.20-s15b/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:6118-6122
  When an attribute-filtered search runs concurrently with `configure_projections`, this validation can pass on the writer connection and then release the lock before the reader transaction prepares the vec0 query. If the projection is dropped/reconciled in that window, `vector_filter_clause` still emits `attr_<hex>=?` for a column that no longer exists, so the search returns an opaque `Storage`/SQLite error instead of the intended typed `InvalidFilter` (or a consistent snapshot result). Move the declaration check into the same reader transaction/snapshot that builds the search SQL, or otherwise hold a schema-stable snapshot across validation and execution.
